==========================
ðŸš€ Git + GitHub Cheat Sheet
==========================

## ðŸ”¹ 1. Initialize Git in a new project

git init

## ðŸ”¹ 2. Stage files for commit

git add . # Stage all files
git add <filename> # Stage specific file

## ðŸ”¹ 3. Commit staged files

git commit -m "Your message" # Create a snapshot

## ðŸ”¹ 4. Connect to GitHub

git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git

# (Verify with)

git remote -v

## ðŸ”¹ 5. Push to GitHub (First Time)

git push -u origin main # Use 'main' or 'master' depending on branch

## ðŸ”¹ 6. Push to GitHub (Next Time)

git push

## ðŸ”¹ 7. Common Commands

git status # Check what's changed
git log --oneline # View commit history
git branch # See branches
git checkout -b new-branch # Create + switch to a new branch
git switch main # Switch back to main
git pull # Pull latest from remote

## ðŸ”¹ 8. Fix Mistakes

git reset HEAD <file> # Unstage a file
git reset --soft HEAD~1 # Undo last commit (keeps changes)
git restore <file> # Discard changes in file
